  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Keep Tsunami-Stricken Isatomae Community Alive</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is to give hope for about 6,000 people in a small tsunami-stricken Tohoku community to be economically reactivated, instead of losing community-based economic activities due to inadequate governmental support to such small communities. People in Isatomae established their shops in a large-sized tent, but it still requires donations to maintain the operation of the community shops. It is just the beginning of rebuilding their community economic activities, and still requires support.</narrative>
  </description>
